The paper deals with the problem of autonomous skill acquisition in an initially unknown environment, which is a common problem in robotics and artificial intelligence. The paper proposes an algorithm that actively discovers the manifold of achievable goals within the sensor space. This involves techniques from machine learning, computer vision, and control theory, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.SY. Among these, cs.AI and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories as they directly deal with autonomous agents and robotics, respectively.
